4232.name: Dice
4232.description: A simple game of chance! Roll 'em!!

4233.name: Knuckle Duster
4233.description: Bestows one of the following functions, Rsk. Evasion, Rsk. Haste or Haste.

4234.name: Hatchling's Level 65 Armor
4234.description: Can be put on by double-clicking. Exclusively used by a Hatchling. H5 Price

4235.name: Hatchling's Level 75 Armor
4235.description: Can be put on by double-clicking. Exclusively used by a Hatchling. H5 Price

4237.name: Hatchling's Level 65 Weapon
4237.description: Can be put on by double-clicking. Exclusively used by a Hatchling. H5 Price

4238.name: Hatchling's Level 75 Weapon
4238.description: Can be put on by double-clicking. Exclusively used by a Hatchling. H5 Price

4239.name: Blade Mold
4239.description: Cargo that Trader Arodin needs to send to the Dark Elves. Find all 20 of them and take them to Trader Tyra.

4240.name: Tyra's Bill
4240.description: A note from Trader Tyra. Take it to Trader Arodin in Gludin Village.

4241.name: Ranger's Report - Part 1
4241.description: First piece of a ranger's report. Find all 4 pieces and take them to Guard Alvah.

4242.name: Ranger's Report - Part 2
4242.description: Second piece of a ranger's report. Find all 4 pieces and take them to Guard Alvah.

4243.name: Ranger's Report - Part 3
4243.description: Third piece of a ranger's report. Find all 4 pieces and take them to Guard Alvah.

4244.name: Ranger's Report - Part 4
4244.description: Fourth piece of a ranger's report. Find all 4 pieces and take them to Guard Alvah.

4245.name: Weapons Trade Contract
4245.description: The contract that was carried by an Ol Mahum General. It is stamped with the Mark of the Dwarves. Take it to Guard Alvah.

4246.name: Attack Directives
4246.description: An operation order that was carried by an Ol Mahum General. Take it to Guard Alvah.

4247.name: Certificate of the Silver Scale Guild
4247.description: Certificate that verifies one's membership to the Silver Scale Guild.

4248.name: Rolento's Cargobox
4248.description: The war supplies that the Dwarven trader Rolento promised to send to Turek orcs. First, show it to Guard Alvah.

4249.name: Ol Mahum Captain's Head
4249.description: A severed head of an Ol Mahum captain. Collect 30 of them and take them to Turek Chief Burai.

4250.name: Jade Crystal
4250.description: Jade gemstone from the Enchanted Valley. Collect them and take them to Bentley of Hunters Village.

4251.name: Ancient Statue of Goddess
4251.description: A statue of a goddess from an old empire that has been discovered in the cemetery. Take it to Priestess Flownia of Town of Aden.

4252.name: GalfRedo Romer's Bust
4252.description: A statue created by the ancient sculptor Berona. Take it to Trader Galibredo of the Town of Oren.

4253.name: Eye of the Shadow
4253.description: Collect 50 eyes of the Shadow and take them to Warehouse Keeper Sorint.

4254.name: Certificate of Participation: Battle Royal
4254.description: The certificate that allows one to participate in a Battle Royal. This game is played by grade 1 members of the Coin Collectors Club.

4255.name: Trade Cargo
4255.description: The cargo boxes that have been robbed from the wagon of the Trade Guild. Collect 30 of them and take them to Guard Weisz.

4256.name: Agnes's Holy Symbol
4256.description: The Crucifix of the goddess of Einhasad. This article was left by Priestess Agnes after her death. Take it along with Agnes's Rosary to Priest Adonius.

4257.name: Agnes's Rosary
4257.description: A rosary used while praying. It was left by Priestess Agnes after her death. Take it along with the Crucifix of the goddess of Einhasad to Priest Adonius.

4258.name: Sinister Totem
4258.description: A black colored totem that exudes an evil aura. Take it to High Priestess Levian.

4259.name: Bear Skin
4259.description: The pelts obtained by hunting bears. Collect 20 of them and take them to Grocer Pano of Floran Village.

4260.name: Enku Orc's Head
4260.description: Beheaded head of an Enku Orc. Collect 100 of them and take them to Orc Lady Jennifer.

4261.name: Orc Heads Bouquet -1
4261.description: A bouquet made by tying 100 orc heads together. On behalf of Jennifer who is shy, deliver it to High Prefect Drikus.

4262.name: Orc Heads Bouquet -2
4262.description: A bouquet made by tying 100 orc heads together. On behalf of Jennifer who is shy, deliver it to Priest Manuel.

4263.name: Orc Heads Bouquet -3
4263.description: A bouquet made by tying 100 orc heads together. On behalf of Jennifer who is shy, deliver it to Vuku Chief Driko.

4264.name: Orc Heads Bouquet -4
4264.description: A bouquet made by tying 100 orc heads together. On behalf of Jennifer who is shy, deliver it to Seer Somak.

4265.name: Orc Heads Bouquet -5
4265.description: A bouquet made by tying 100 orc heads together. On behalf of Jennifer who is shy, deliver it to Prefect Dowki.

4266.name: Orc Heads Bouquet -6
4266.description: A bouquet made by tying 100 orc heads together. On behalf of Jennifer who is shy, deliver it to Warden Endrigo.

4267.name: Orc Heads Bouquet -7
4267.description: A bouquet made by tying 100 orc heads together. On behalf of Jennifer who is shy, deliver it to Captain Lucas.

4268.name: Jennifer's Box
4268.description: The box that a man who is smitten by Orc Lady Jennifer asked this to be delivered to her. What do you think is in the box...?

4269.name: Articles of Dead Heroes
4269.description: The articles of dead soldiers who were sent as an expeditionary force 1,000 years ago. These articles have been collected by hunting cave servants. Take them to Antharas Watchman Gilmore.

4270.name: Old Key
4270.description: An article left by a dead soldier. His descendent Sir Kristof Rodemai is living in Town of Giran. Take it to him.

4271.name: Old Hilt
4271.description: An article left by a dead soldier. His descendant Duelist Kaien is living in the Town of Oren. Take it to him.

4272.name: Totem Necklace
4272.description: An article left by a dead soldier. His descendent, High Prefect Garvarentz, is living in Hunters Village. Take it to him.

4273.name: Einhasad Crucifix
4273.description: An article left by a dead soldier. Take it to High Priest Orven of Einhasad Temple in Town of Aden where the dead soldier used to be stationed.

4274.name: Victim's Arm Bone
4274.description: The arm bone of a victim who has been eaten by a Crokian. Collect the five types of bones and take them to Xenovia.

4275.name: Victim's Thigh Bone
4275.description: The thigh bone of a victim who has been eaten by a Crokian. Collect the five types of bones and take them to Xenovia.

4276.name: Victim's Skull
4276.description: The skull of a victim who has been eaten alive by a Crokian. Collect the five types of bones and take them to Xenovia.

4277.name: Victim's Rib Bone
4277.description: The rib bone of a victim who has been eaten by a Crokian. Collect the five types of bones and take them to Xenovia.

4278.name: Victim's Spine
4278.description: The spine of a victim who has been eaten by a Crokian. Collect the five types of bones and take them to Xenovia.

4279.name: Jar of Bones
4279.description: An urn that contains the bones of all the victims. Ask Mad Doctor Orpheus to resurrect the victims.

4280.name: Useless Bone Pieces
4280.description: Useless bone pieces obtained after hunting Crokians. If you take them to Orpheus, perhaps something good will happen...?

4281.name: Powder to Summon Dead Souls
4281.description: The magic powder bought from Magister Xenovia. Throw it along with the victims' bones into the Psychic Medium's Urn.

4282.name: Sack of the Dead
4282.description: A sack containing a victim's soul. An urn was possessed by the victim's soul. Take it to Locksmith Dorothy.

4283.name: Frog Prince
4283.description: What are you waiting for? You promised to help me! Release me from this curse immediately! I must regain my appearance as soon as possible!!!

4284.name: Fly Powder
4284.description: Powder made by grinding dried flies. Use it when you fail in your attempt to transform a frog.

4285.name: Calculator
4285.description: The latest model of calculator. Take it to Blacksmith Brunon.

4286.name: Gemstone Beast's Crystal
4286.description: Crystal obtained by slaying a gemstone beast. Collect 10 of these and take them to Blacksmith Silvera.

4287.name: Titan's Powerstone
4287.description: The Titan's Powerstone that has been extracted from the corpse of a Giant. Take it to Magister Hanellin.

4288.name: Hanellin's 1st Letter
4288.description: A letter that Hanellin entrusted you with. Take it to Magister Harne of the Dark Elven Village and receive your next assignment from her.

4289.name: Hanellin's 2nd Letter
4289.description: A letter that Hanellin entrusted you with. Take it to Claudia Athebaldt of Town of Aden and receive your next assignment from her.

4290.name: Hanellin's 3rd Letter
4290.description: A letter that Hanellin entrusted you with. Take it to Martien of the Town of Giran and receive your next assignment from him.

4291.name: 1st Key of Ark
4291.description: The key that was found upon the corpse of the guardian of the sacred ark. Use this key to open the sacred ark and retrieve the sacred object.

4292.name: 2nd Key of Ark
4292.description: The key that was taken after killing Elberos, the guardian of the sacred ark. Use the key to open the sacred ark and retrieve the sacred object.

4293.name: 3rd Key of Ark
4293.description: The key that was taken after killing Shadowfang, the guardian of the sacred ark. Use the key to open the sacred ark and retrieve the sacred object.

4294.name: White Fabric
4294.description: A large piece of white cloth given by Magister Hanellin. Kill the Platinum Tribe Shamans and Overlords and soak the cloth with their blood.

4295.name: Blooded Fabric
4295.description: A piece of cloth soaked in the blood of angels and the Platinum race. Hanellin has told you that in order to challenge Baium, you must wrap this blood-soaked cloth around your body.

4296.name: Order of Gosta
4296.description: The order states that you should hunt Tasaba Lizardmen and Tasaba Lizardman Shaman and bring back their fangs as proof.

4297.name: Lizard Fang
4297.description: The fangs that have been collected as proofs that Tasaba Lizardmen and Tasaba Lizardman Shaman have been hunted.

4298.name: Barrel of League
4298.description: This seems to be the cargo that was stolen from Iason Heine's wagon by Tasaba Lizardmen.

4299.name: Operation Document - 1/10
4299.description: This document was found in the cargo of the Trade Guild. The document contains various information regarding Innadril. How could this have happened...?
